Seems that I've run into a problem with a customer generating a thread dump on a windows machine when they are running JIRA as a service. 

Following [this documentation|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Generating+a+Thread+Dump] they get the error message when generating:
{code}
C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.6.0_27\bin>jstack -l 4404
4404: Not enough storage is available to process this command
{code}

I looked this up and found that [here|http://stackoverflow.com/questions/906620/jstack-and-not-enough-storage-is-available-to-process-this-command] the command *psexec -s* needs to be used. As per the user quote seems that this has effected Windows machines from Vista onwards.

{quote}
It appears that on Vista and later jstack doesn't work against services because of the user context.
{quote}

